~~ The following items are for help
~~ If the tag does not have TITLE in it then they may be up 
~~ to 13 rows long and they all can be up to 44 wide.


~~ Rows = 1 
MAINHELPTITLE
Main Help



~~ Rows = 11
MAINHELP
Acceleration adjusts the rate of pointer 
movement according to the speed of mouse 
movement.

Sensitivity sets the ratio of mouse versus
pointer movement.

Press Esc to exit any window.
Press F1 for Help.
Press Page Up and Page Down to browse 
      through help.





~~ Rows = 1
ORIHELPTITLE
Orientation Help



~~ Rows = 4
ORIENTHELP
The Orientation Window lets you orient the
movement of your mouse.  When you set 
Orientation, you tell the software which 
way is up.




~~ Rows = 1
SELECTHELPTITLE
Button Selection Help



~~ Rows = 10
SELECTHELP
The Buttons Window lets you set the primary
and secondary mouse buttons.

ClickLock, available for the BallPoint 
mouse, lets you drag by clicking the button
that is not primary or secondary. Click any
button to stop the drag.





~~ Rows = 1
POINTHELPTITLE
Pointer Options Help



~~ Rows = 14
POINTHELP
Pointer Options let you set the size and 
color of the pointer.

Pointer Growth, available when a medium or
large pointer is selected, helps you keep 
track of the pointer on the screen.

Threshold sets the mouse speed needed to 
make the pointer grow, and Delay sets the 
time period needed to make the pointer 
return to normal.




~~ Rows = 0

